JOHANNESBURG - It’s peak holiday season in most countries around the world, and while millions of holiday makers will set off on their journey’s around the globe, only a select few will travel in luxurious private jets. eNCA reporter Riante Naidoo visited a local air charter company to see how the rich and famous get around when they are on holiday. She got the VVIP treatment, rubbed shoulders with cabin crew members who have served royalty and, most importantly, found out how much it costs to fly like the wealthy elite do. eNCA